    "permit_type": "Land Use ReviewType 1x procedureHR - Historic Resource Review",
    "work_description": "Approval of minor alterations to a non-original external stair at north side of the Landmark Church of St. Michael the Archangel church building. The proposed work includes rebuilding a concrete wall adjacent to the stair, extending the existing fence and concrete curb, and adding a walkway from the stairs to the parking area. This proposal will result in the external stairs exiting into the fenced parking area internal to the site, rather than to the adjacent sidewalk. Approval per plans, Exhibits C-1 through C-6, signed and dated October 9, 2024, subject to the following conditions: A.As part of the building permit application submittal, the following development-related conditions (B through D) must be noted on each of the four required site plans or included as a sheet in the numbered set of plans. The sheet on which this information appears must be labeled \"ZONING COMPLIANCE PAGE- Case File LU 24-067468 HR.\" All requirements must be graphically represented on the site plan, landscape, or other required plan and must be labeled \"REQUIRED.\" B.At the time of building permit submittal, a signed Certificate of Compliance form (https://www.portland.gov/ppd/documents/design-and-historic-resource-review-approvals-certificate-compliance) must be submitted to ensure the permit plans comply with the Design/Historic Resource Review decision and approved exhibits. C. No field changes allowed. D.A skim coat shall be added to the new CMU wall to match the finish on the existing adjacent concrete wall.",
